<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-935-944  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 935 944.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacUser  Jan 1990 v6 n1 p71(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Interactive Population Statistical System. (Software Review)(Pinstripe Picks)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wiggins, Robert R.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   PSRC Software (products).andO;Product:   IPSS (Statistical software).andO;Topic:     Statistical SoftwareEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Interactive Population Statistical System IPSS is a statistical, simulation,and modeling program with some graphics capabilities that are designed tohelp demographics specialists project human populations.andP;  You enterinformation on age composition, fertility rates, survival rates, and/ormigration, and you can even add a special rate to study its effect on thepopulation (cancer rates are used in the example files).andP;  Once the data isentered, you can run projections and get results in tabular or graphic form.andO;Some of the graphing methods available here are lexis surfaces, 100-percentsurfaces, and 3-D population pyramids.andM;The one weakness in IPSS is data entry; IPSS includes no facility other thancopy and paste for importing data to other programs.andP;  This is doubly oddbecause the IPSS provides several ways to export data.andM;Overall, IPSS is a good system with a strong quantitative background (thePascal code for the projections and life-table analysis is even included.andP;  inthe documentation).andM;Requires Macintosh Plus or later.andP;  Plus or SE version, $295; 68020/68030version, $395.andP;  PSRC Software, Population and Society Research Center,Bowling Green State University, Bowling Green, OH 43403; (419) 372-8648.andO;</TEXT></DOC>